    "body": "Fix `10-block-scaled-matmul.py` for `mxfp4` and `mixed` formats by initializing the cuBLAS scale return values to `None` when those formats do not have a cuBLAS comparison path.\r\n\r\nPreviously, `initialize_block_scaled()` only assigned `a_scale_cublas` and `b_scale_cublas` for `mxfp8` and `nvfp4`, but returned them unconditionally. This caused `UnboundLocalError` when running the tutorial benchmark with `--format mxfp4` or `--format mixed`.\r\n\r\nNow you can do: \r\n```\r\npython3 -u 10-block-scaled-matmul.py --format mxfp4 --K_range 512 8192 --bench\r\npython3 -u 10-block-scaled-matmul.py --format mixed --K_range 512 8192 --bench\r\n```",
    "created_at": "2026-04-28T02:23:17Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-04-28T14:20:15Z",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-28T14:20:15Z",
